\lim_{x \to +\infty} \left(\frac{3x+2}{3x-2}\right)^{2x}
\exp\left(\dfrac{8}{3}\right)
\lim_{x \to +\infty}\left(\frac{3x+2}{3x-2}\right)^{2x}=\lim_{x \to +\infty}\exp\left(\ln\left(\left(\frac{3x+2}{3x-2}\right)^{2x}\right)\right)\\ =\lim_{x \to +\infty}\exp\left(2x\ln\left(\frac{3x+2}{3x-2}\right)\right) =\exp{\left(\lim_{x \to +\infty}2x\times\lim_{x \to +\infty}\ln\left(\frac{3x+2}{3x-2}\right)\right)}
t=3x-2
x=(t+2)/3
 \frac{3x+2}{3x-2}=\frac{3x-2+4}{3x-2}=1+\frac{4}{3x-2} 
 \lim_{t\to\infty}\left(1+\frac{4}{t}\right)^{2\frac{t+2}{3}}= \left(\lim_{t\to\infty}   \left(1+\frac{4}{t}\right)^t\cdot   \lim_{t\to\infty}\left(1+\frac{4}{t}\right)^2 \right)^{2/3} 
 \left(\frac{3x+2}{3x-2}\right)^{2x} =\left(\frac{\left(1+\frac{2}{3x}\right)^x}{\left(1-\frac{2}{3x}\right)^x}\right)^2 
